This executive order, issued by President Donald Trump on June 30, 2017, establishes the revival and composition of the National Space Council. The purpose of the Council is to advise and assist the President regarding national space policy and strategy. The Council will be composed of various members, including the Vice President, Secretaries of State, Defense, Commerce, and Transportation, as well as the heads of other executive departments and agencies. The Council's functions include reviewing and developing US government space policy, fostering cooperation among different sectors, advising on international space activities, and resolving policy matters. The Chair of the Council will serve as the President's principal advisor on space policy and strategy. The Council will also convene a Users' Advisory Group composed of non-Federal representatives involved in aeronautical and space activities. The order includes administrative provisions for support and resources for the Council and requires the Council to submit an annual report on the assessment and recommendations for US space policy and strategy.